name: What is Infinite Cross?
note:
<SGDescription:\\C[14]Infinite Cross\\C[0] is a Project that consist of many stories in various multimedia.
All stories that is labelled "Infinite Cross" shares the same settings and history.
In the world of \\C[14]Infinite Cross\\C[0], The world has been divided to 3 subworlds: 
\\C[1]Noian\\C[0], which is similar to the world in Real Life where technology and science reigns supreme; 
\\C[1]Galilean\\C[0], a world of ash, steam and perpetual motion machines; 
and \\C[1]Turian\\C[0], a world of sword, fantasy and sorcery. 
The means of transporting between worlds has been easily archived in the early 20th century.>
<SGDescription2:In this partuliar game, the Main Character Duo is a Human from Noian, and a Fairy from Turian. 
This story mainly happens in a mansion in a Turian town. 
Galilean isn't featured in this game in any shape or form, sorry about that, Steampunk fans!
Maybe next time! I promise!>    
<SGCategory:Infinite Cross>

name: Humans
note:
<SGDescription:Humans are just that, Humans. Biologically, all humans from the 3 worlds are the same.
However, Humans that were born and raised in Turian has higher ability regarding sorcery.
While there are Noian Sorcerers and Enchanters, these sights are pretty rare. Plus, those people are almost always raised in Turian anyways.

In this game, all characters aside from Chris, Vivian and Monto are Turian born and raised humans.

Chris is also a human, though born and raised in Noian.>
<SGCategory:Infinite Cross>

name: Fairies
note:
<SGDescription:Fairies are humanoid creatures that's unique in Turian. They are materizations of this world's various concepts.
These could be traditional elements such like "Metal", "Fire", "Water", or concepts such like "Writing", "Music", or even "Metaphysics".
Generally, they process special abilities related to their element or concept.

On the surface, they look like pre-teen boys/girls. However don't get fooled by their appearance.
Fairies have a really long lifespan, and when they expire, as long as the element or concept tied to them is not disappearing, they can reincarnate endlessly.
Also, since they're essentally conceptal, normal means cannot harm them.
In a sense, they are almost immortal.>
<SGDescription2:Thus, they're highly intelligent and curious, after the 3 World's borders was crossed in Early 20th Century, a huge number of fairies migrated to Noian and Galilean and found jobs related to technology.
Since it's to them, something brand new compared to the Turian Sorceries.
It's not a rare sight seeing a Fairy Programmer in Noian, for example. (Plus, Fairy Programmers perform better due to their nature.)
While they can't use their abilities often due to leaving their natural habitat, they still proved to be a great addition to Noian and Galilean's societies.
In this game, the only Fairy character is \\C[1]Vivian\\C[0]. You don't want anymore unkillable characters in a murder mystery game, do you?>
<SGCategory:Infinite Cross>

name: Dragons
note:
<SGDescription:Turian is a world of fantasy, of course there would be dragons.
However, rather than being a huge lizard-like creature depicted in various multimedia, Turian Dragons are humanoid.

Generally, Dragons are naturally gifted \\C[1]Enchanters\\C[0], that is to say, they have the innate ability of putting a piece of sorcery into an item.>

<SGDescription2:Be that a piece of paper, a piece of weapon, or even mundane items such like a keychain.
If they will it, they can make them do different things that's equivalent to a spell cast.

While the normal humans can learn everything about Enchanting, their limited stamina will pose as a problem.
For example, Dragons can freely enchant a summoning sorcery into paper spells and cast them instantly.
Which is far more than what a human Enchanter can possibly do.>
<SGCategory:Infinite Cross>

name: Chris
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Chrisopher Lowe
Age: 24
A self-claimed freelance photographer.
If asked more about that claim, he'll make another claim that he still lives on his parent's money.
However, this is all a lie.
Chris is actually a private detective, the reason he hides this fact is unknown.
He met Vivian some time ago in an incident, and Vivian took an interest in him.
As a result, he is looking to expand his business for this additional addition.
It's very troubling, but Vivian is cute and useful so as a sidekick so why not. 
And yes, \\C[14]he's a guy.\\C[0]>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Chris>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

name: Vivian
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Vixian
Age: 462
A Turian Fairy.
Her concept is "The Past".

She got bored of staying in Turian, so like most of her brathren that did so, migrated to Noian.
However, eventually she got bored of technology too, probably due to her concept.

Instead of wanting to learn something new, she choose to sate her curiousity in Noian culture.
And she took a liking to those Noir Detective Stories.

She met Chris in a case as a witness of an important event, and took a liking to him ever since.>

<SGDescription2:While Chris explained to her multiple times that Noir Detectives are a thing of fiction and past,
plus being a detective's sidekick means heavy legwork and writing, 
those facts does not discourage her at all.

Her ability born from her concept, is the ability of seeing the past.
More precisely, she can access any point of the past in a given zone.
Since Chris is a detective, this ability almost looks like cheating to him.
But nevertheless he made use of this to his full potential.
After all, after knowing the final answer, it'll be much easier solving a problem.>

<SGDescription3:However, looking into the past is very taxing on Vivian's mind since the images of past would intervene her ability of perceiving the present as well.
So most of the time she wear an enchanted hood to block her own ability.

While she can also project what she saw in the past to Chris, it's even more taxing for Chris since humans aren't built for looking into multiple time frames.
So Vivian would only pick the most important moments in the past to project.

They really make a good team.>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Vivian>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

name: Monto
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Wilson Nilmont
Age: 26
Master Dragon Enchanter.
Was involved in a student transfer program between Turian and Noian.
As a result, he became Chris's classmate for 4 years.
His speciality is summoning and alchemy.
Basically, invloves creating something from nothing.
He often release his products for free to the people needing help,
As a result is quite famous in the area.
Under his serious persona, he's actually sort of a Trickster, and often take pleasure on pranking his close friends.
Even his mansion was built to be triggering everyone's OCD.>

<SGDescription2:Recently for some unknown reason he summoned his old classmate, Chris, 
and some other related people to his mansion.

He admits to Chris in his inviation that some cult named "The Imbalancers" wants his life taken.

It seems one of his "tricks" finally went too far..>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Monto>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

name: Alma
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Alma Galway
Age: 31
A professor with unmatched knowledge on exotic cultures.
Currently working in a university Monto fundraised.

Monto invited him due to his knowledge of "The Imbalancers".

However, his knowledge, while valuable, is still limited due to the hidden nature of the cult.>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Alma>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

name: Loyd
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Loyd Fleming
Age: 26
One of Monto's close friends.
Specialzes at barrier sorcery.
Thus earned the title "Defender of the Academy".

No matter how ruthless the possible attackers from the cult can get, if it cannot hit, it means nothing.
Which is where Loyd comes in.>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Loyd>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

name: Jannie
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Jannie Meighan
Age: 25
A ill-tempered lady late to the party.
She perfers to keep her distance to others,
The reason why Monto invited her is unknown.

Seems to be a master on Elemental Sorcery.>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Jannie>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

name: Alfred
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Alfred Farrell
Age: 28
Alchemist for Hire.
He's one of the top providers of Monto's materials.
After all, to make enchantments, one needs items to store the sorcery pieces on.
Especially since Monto distributes his enchantments instead of recovering them, 
that means he constantly need more materials.

Alfred is here solely for delivering Monto's needed amulets, but Monto insisted him to stay for dinner.>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Alfred>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

name: Vera
note:
<SGDescription:Full Name: Vera Skidd
Age: 14
While normally only Dragons can access the full range of enchant sorcery, there are always rare cases of human enchanters. That were born gifted.
Vera is one of them.
Her family noticed Vera's spark on Enchanting, but cannot afford the proper education.
Thus Monto took her in as a student.

She's always complaining that Monto is treating her like a little kid (which she is), 
but the truth is that Monto treats her like his little sister.
Which, to her, is no better.>
<SGCategory:Characters>
<SGPicture:Vera>
<SGPicturePosition:under>
<SGPictureScale:0.5>
<SGPictureAlign:right>

description:
An invitation that has 2 pages.
View this in the CODEX.
name: Invitation Letter
note:
<WordWrap>
<SGDescription:My old friends,
I believe I'm in grave danger.
Somebody I trust informed me that I've become a target of the cult "The Imbalancers".

Because of this development,
I have something very important to tell all my friends,
please come to my mansion while we can discuss in depth.>
<SGDescription2:And to you, Chris, my old classmate,
I do not think this is a coincidence.
According to professionals, this cult--
"The Imbalancers", 
hid themselves a century ago,
before you and me are even born.
Perhaps your fairy friend would know more about them?
Nevertheless, please come,
since I know you've have nothing else better to do.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
There's only one entrance to Monto's Room.
There's no way one can come in by other ways.
name: Monto's Room #1
note:
<SGDescription:There's only 1 entrance and possible exit to Monto's room.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
According to the Maids,
The Garden is one of the Blind Spots for a certain enchantment.
name: Blind Spot #1
note:
<SGDescription:Seems Mondo put down some sort of Enchantment.
It will only work indoors, so the Garden, being outdoor, becomes a blind spot.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
Sorcery that builds a conceptual contract.
Contract enforces certain rules. View more in CODEX.
name: Contract Sorcery
note:
<SGDescription:A Contract sorcery involves, obviously a contract.
It's mainly used to control summoned creatures. 
For example, it's not uncommon for sorcerers to summon and contract fairies.
However, contracts can also be conceptual, such like forbidding a certain behaviour.
As long as the contract is in effect, said behaviour will have no effect.

In advanced enchanting, contracts can also be bound to an enchantment.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
A secret cult that seems to want Monto dead.
However it's so secret that only a few have heard of it.
name: The Imbalancers
note:
<SGDescription:An evil cult that operates in secret.
Seems to worship anything not balanced.
Or in other words, breaking the Status Quo.
However, they can't stand people who do inbalanced things but are not part of them.

Monto built his mansion in a certain way to screw with people, 
however, it seems because of that, 
the Imbalancers marked him a heretic,
and wants his life taken.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
In this mansion, Teleportation and Direct Damage Sorcery
are forbidden under Contract Enchantments.
name: Monto's Contracts #1
note:
<SGDescription:Teleportation is the sorcery that allows one to instantly travel from A to B.
Direct Damaging Sorceries refer to sorceries that's elemental and/or curse oriented.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
There's only one entrance to Monto's Room.
There's no way one can come in by other ways.
name: Monto's Room #2
note:
<SGDescription:There's only 1 entrance and possible exit to Monto's room.
Since Monto claims that he blocked most of the sorcery from casting,
We can also rule out the possiblity that the murderer teleports in and out from the room.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
According to Vera,
One of the Enchantments in the mansion is broken.
name: Enchantment Status #1
note:
<SGDescription:While damaging Sorcery is forbidden in the mansion.
It seems enchantments can be easily broken using physical means.
However, seeing that Vera seems to be able to repair them, it's probably not a big deal?>
<SGCategory:Clues>

description:
The only teleporter that goes two-ways,
From the Kitchen to the Dining Room.
name: The Only Teleporter
note:
<SGDescription:Honestly? I don't think this is related to our case, we'll see.>
<SGCategory:Clues>

name: "Sorcery"
note:
<SGDescription:There's one thing very important regarding the setting:
\\C[14]There's no Magic in Turian.\\C[0]
The word is Sorcery.
While Noian and Galilean people sometimes use the word Magic to refer to Turian Sorcery.
But there's a key difference.
In Turian, \\C[14]Magic is something sorcery cannot achieve.\\C[0]
Thus, no one in Turian refer their skills as Magic.
It's kinda like the difference between giant panda and lesser pandas...>
<SGCategory:Infinite Cross>

description:
A common sliver coin, enchanted with alchemy.
While it's just a coin, it's unnaturally heavy.
name: Vera's Special
note:
<SGDescription:On closer inspection, this coin is much heavier than usual.
It's not iron or copper... Could it be..Platinum?
Also, for some reason, if I toss this coin, it'll always land Heads up. >
<SGCategory:Story Item>

description:
It's like a smartphone, but even smarter.
I can access this from the main menu.
name: CODEX 2900
note:
<SGDescription:The latest model of the CODEX series.
It's a Noian Cyber gadget, but is built using technologies from Turian and Galilean as well.
For starters, it can automatically gather important information and record it in its storage.
So it warrants frequent checking, like what you're doing right now!>
<SGCategory:Story Item>
